      • predecessor

        default java.lang.Long predecessor​(long x)
        Returns the largest key in the subset of keys that are strictly smaller than x.
        predecessor(x) = max{y in S | y < x}
        It follows the rule predecessor(x) = select(rank(x)-1)
        Parameters:
        x - The query.
        Returns:
        The largest key in the set that is smaller than the query.

      • successor

        default java.lang.Long successor​(long x)
        Returns the smallest key in the subset of keys that are larger or equal to x.
        succ(x) = min{y ∈ S | y ≤ x}
        It follows the rule successor(x) = select(rank(x))
        Parameters:
        x - The query.
        Returns:
        x if it is in the set. Otherwise returns the smallest key in the set that is larger than x.
